quran[4]{c,v,t}:
  8,45,"O believers! When you encounter an enemy in a combat, be firm and frequently remember Allah so that you may be successful"
  8,46,"Obey Allah and His Messenger and do not argue with one another, lest you lose courage and weaken your strength. Show patience, surely Allah is on the side of the patient"
  8,47,Do not be like those who started from their homes recklessly in order to be seen by everybody and debar others from the Way of Allah. Allah encompasses all their actions
  8,48,"Remember when Satan made their actions seem attractive to them, and said: \"No one from mankind can overcome you today, for I will be at hand to help you.\" Yet when the two armies came within sight of each other he turned upon his heels saying: \" I am done with you, for I can see what you cannot. I fear Allah, for Allah is severe in punishment"